-- Central European Media Tumbles for Second Day After Loss Widens
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-02-23T09:12:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/central-european-media-tumbles-for-second-day-after-loss-widens.html
Central European Media Enterprises
Ltd. (CETV)  fell for a second day in Czech trading after the television
broadcaster said yesterday its fourth-quarter loss widened.  The stock tumbled as much as 19 percent and traded down 11
percent to 136.6 koruna by 10:07 a.m. in Prague, poised for its
biggest one-day drop in more than three months. In  New York , its
domestic market, Central European Media fell 18 percent
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
